{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":323,"text":"I'll tell you a little bit about my story\nand who I am."},{"time":2788,"text":"I'm a fashion photographer\nbased in New York City."},{"time":5436,"text":"I've worked for lots \nof different magazines in New York,"},{"time":8258,"text":"I've worked for Elle and for Marie Claire,"},{"time":13056,"text":"and for Interview and for GQ,"},{"time":14998,"text":"and I got to work \nwith some really beautiful people."},{"time":17505,"text":"My studio is in New York,"},{"time":18826,"text":"but I also lived in Milan\nfor about eight years,"},{"time":21047,"text":"and in Paris as well,"},{"time":22746,"text":"and worked for the house \nof Yves St. Laurent."},{"time":25644,"text":"I also did portraiture as well."},{"time":30475,"text":"I've worked for lots \nof different magazines,"},{"time":32904,"text":"lots of great clients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34653,"text":"But I was always told,\nevery single day, who was beautiful."},{"time":37294,"text":"I was forced to work"},{"time":38826,"text":"within certain parameters \nof the beauty standard."},{"time":41268,"text":"I was told, \"This is the most \namazing model of the moment,"},{"time":43841,"text":"you've got to photograph her."},{"time":45227,"text":"She's incredible, you've got to.\""},{"time":47305,"text":"And then the next season,\nit would change again,"},{"time":49421,"text":"and I'd have to shift my ideas of beauty,"},{"time":51768,"text":"and so we'd go to the next model,"},{"time":53474,"text":"and it was kind of really crazy,\nbecause I'm an artist."},{"time":56205,"text":"I saw beauty everywhere."},{"time":57849,"text":"I didn't see beauty \njust on a magazine cover."},{"time":60769,"text":"I did a shoot with, of \ncourse, Cindy, for Revlon,"},{"time":63764,"text":"and really fantastic, beautiful people."},{"time":66602,"text":"But I thought,"},{"time":67888,"text":"someone's always telling me \nwho's beautiful."},{"time":70590,"text":"And I was kind of frustrated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72086,"text":"I left my studio one \nafternoon in New York,"},{"time":73840,"text":"and I was walking down Park Avenue,"},{"time":75461,"text":"and I saw, waiting for a bus \nat the corner of Park and 20th,"},{"time":78552,"text":"this gorgeous kid."},{"time":80593,"text":"She had long, white, beautiful hair,\nand pale, pale skin."},{"time":84406,"text":"She had a genetic condition \ncalled albinism."},{"time":87109,"text":"I didn't know much about it, \nbut she was stunning,"},{"time":88939,"text":"and I'd never met \na model like this before."},{"time":90721,"text":"And I went to grab her and say,"},{"time":92281,"text":"\"I have to take your photograph, \nyou're amazing!\""},{"time":94431,"text":"And the bus came, she got on, \nand then she took off,"},{"time":96392,"text":"and I was really glad because she was 12,"},{"time":98413,"text":"and I'd be in prison at the moment.\n(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":100324,"text":"But really, it was \nextraordinary to see this kid."},{"time":103057,"text":"So I continued right down to Union Square,"},{"time":105505,"text":"to the huge Barnes and Noble,"},{"time":106916,"text":"and started pulling any books,\nor any information I could"},{"time":109548,"text":"about this genetic condition, albinism."},{"time":111644,"text":"And I found really kind of sad images."},{"time":113975,"text":"I didn't find images of this kid."},{"time":115673,"text":"I found images of people \nsitting in hospital beds, looking sad,"},{"time":119171,"text":"looking downtrodden, \njust images of despair."},{"time":122742,"text":"I found images \nof a bright red eye, the albino eye."},{"time":126105,"text":"I'm thinking, \nthis kid had beautiful blue eyes,"},{"time":128320,"text":"she didn't have red eyes."},{"time":129785,"text":"And then I started seeing \nimages from Africa,"},{"time":131812,"text":"where kids were surrounded by tribes \npointing spears at them"},{"time":135322,"text":"or in cancer wards and clinics,"},{"time":137261,"text":"or they're just in beds, \nand images of illness,"},{"time":140114,"text":"of sadness, of sickness."},{"time":142107,"text":"And then, I started, of course,"},{"time":143661,"text":"going through\nthose same medical textbooks,"},{"time":145161,"text":"and started finding \nthese typical images"},{"time":147362,"text":"of kids and adults in their underwear, \nagainst walls in doctor's offices,"},{"time":150996,"text":"with the black bar across their eyes \nsaying \"disease.\""},{"time":154118,"text":"This is a disease, defined by a disease."},{"time":156572,"text":"And I was like, this is crazy."},{"time":159186,"text":"And then I started going into it further,"},{"time":160964,"text":"looking on the Internet,"},{"time":162308,"text":"and all these different medical textbooks,"},{"time":164068,"text":"and everything was so sad, \nand so negative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166978,"text":"I then started finding images \nof the albino freak family in the circus,"},{"time":171125,"text":"and then of course, \nall the movie references,"},{"time":173145,"text":"from \"Powder,\" who had albinism because\nhis mother was struck by lightning,"},{"time":177835,"text":"to \"The Princess Bride\" and \nto \"The Matrix Reloaded,\""},{"time":181467,"text":"there were the ghost-like twins \nthat came in and wreaked havoc,"},{"time":184157,"text":"and destroyed things and then disappeared."},{"time":186552,"text":"Even most recently, \"The Da Vinci Code,\""},{"time":188808,"text":"there was like the evil albino \ndriving around Paris at night,"},{"time":191698,"text":"killing people, shooting at people."},{"time":193944,"text":"Well, I found out, through my research,"},{"time":195949,"text":"that people with albinism \nhave a visual impairment."},{"time":198193,"text":"There's always vision, \nbut they're considered legally blind."},{"time":201507,"text":"So they certainly wouldn't be driving \naround Paris at night"},{"time":203831,"text":"shooting at anybody\nand expect to hit anything."},{"time":205971,"text":"So I'm thinking, this is crazy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208358,"text":"So I contact NOAH."},{"time":209852,"text":"Now, NOAH is the National Organization \nfor Albinism and Hypopigmentation."},{"time":214753,"text":"It's a support group for people \nliving with this condition,"},{"time":217229,"text":"and their families."},{"time":218575,"text":"And I'm like, \"Hey, I'm a \nfashion photographer."},{"time":220611,"text":"Let's show the world \nthe beauty of albinism!\""},{"time":222847,"text":"And they said, \"Get lost.\""},{"time":224661,"text":"And I'm pretty persistent. I'm \nlike, \"Won't you talk to me?\""},{"time":227003,"text":"And they made it very clear to me"},{"time":228934,"text":"about their fears of exploitation,"},{"time":231135,"text":"that every time there \nwas a magazine article"},{"time":232884,"text":"that came out about a kid with albinism,"},{"time":234753,"text":"it was a story about a victim."},{"time":236460,"text":"It was sad, or it was exploitative,"},{"time":238915,"text":"or sensational — never \npositive, always negative."},{"time":242316,"text":"And I said, \"Okay, well then, \nwhat do we do here?\""},{"time":245351,"text":"So, let's form a nontraditional partnership —"},{"time":248067,"text":"fashion photographer, \ngenetic support group —"},{"time":250685,"text":"and we'll work together."},{"time":252092,"text":"And you can keep an eye on me"},{"time":253150,"text":"to make sure that we create \nsomething positive and powerful,"},{"time":256228,"text":"showing the world the beauty of albinism."},{"time":258797,"text":"And they said okay."},{"time":259988,"text":"And I was like, fantastic, let's do this!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":261694,"text":"So in walks the first person \nI'm about to photograph."},{"time":263834,"text":"Her name is Christine, \nand Christine is a knockout."},{"time":267421,"text":"Long white hair, really tall. \nShe's stunning."},{"time":270196,"text":"She walks into my studio."},{"time":271968,"text":"The way that she walks in, though, \ninstead of this gorgeous girl,"},{"time":275005,"text":"she walks in like this, her head's down,"},{"time":277538,"text":"shoulders hunched, one-word answers, \nshe looks down, no eye contact."},{"time":282068,"text":"This kid has been teased her whole life \nbecause of her difference."},{"time":286020,"text":"And it was so apparent in the fact \nthat it left her with zero self-esteem."},{"time":291852,"text":"And I'm thinking, oh, this \nkid is just so fragile."},{"time":295879,"text":"And just the day before, \nI was shooting Cindy"},{"time":297752,"text":"on the same set, in my studio."},{"time":299801,"text":"I'm thinking well, \nI have to be so careful with her — no,"},{"time":303391,"text":"out of respect for this gorgeous kid,"},{"time":305151,"text":"I'm going to photograph her \nlike I would anybody else."},{"time":306983,"text":"So the fan went on, the music went on,"},{"time":309534,"text":"and I grabbed a mirror \nthat was next to the set,"},{"time":311075,"text":"and I held it up to her, and I said"},{"time":312992,"text":"Christine, look at yourself. \nYou're magnificent."},{"time":317071,"text":"And she looked in the mirror, \nand she got it."},{"time":319852,"text":"And she went from this to that."},{"time":322768,"text":"And that's our Christine, \nand she just exploded in front of the set."},{"time":326480,"text":"By the time she left the studio, \nshe was kissing everybody on both cheeks,"},{"time":330602,"text":"and saying, \"Ciao!\" \nand she was unbelievable."},{"time":333602,"text":"And I saw this transformation \nright in front of the lens,"},{"time":336799,"text":"through photography, \nthat she was now transformed,"},{"time":339596,"text":"with a powerful and positive sense \nof who she is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342943,"text":"The next day, she goes to school,"},{"time":344787,"text":"she's going to change the way \nher community sees her difference."},{"time":347847,"text":"Instead of walking into \nthat classroom like this,"},{"time":350185,"text":"she's walking in like this."},{"time":351608,"text":"So it's all about ambassadors for change."},{"time":354046,"text":"It was extraordinary."},{"time":355104,"text":"And those first images, right after,\nwe did a series of them,"},{"time":357894,"text":"using several individuals \nwith this condition,"},{"time":361327,"text":"they were in Life magazine in 1998."},{"time":364541,"text":"So it was a while ago."},{"time":365911,"text":"It was a cover story, \nit was a five-page spread."},{"time":368153,"text":"It was really a fantastic editorial.\nIt was great; I loved it."},{"time":372325,"text":"Then we used a lot of the images, \nthough, from Life,"},{"time":375632,"text":"and put them in other magazines, \nmagazines worldwide."},{"time":378768,"text":"Magazines in the U.K., in France, \nin Italy and Canada,"},{"time":382435,"text":"and other magazines in the States.\nIt was amazing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385237,"text":"So this is from the U.K., Christine again."},{"time":387475,"text":"Friends Jen and Ruthie are sisters, \nand Kristen."},{"time":390351,"text":"That's Lauren. \nWe did a campaign for sunglasses."},{"time":393913,"text":"A lot of kids with this condition \nare photophobic,"},{"time":396606,"text":"so they have \na real strong light sensitivity."},{"time":399018,"text":"So we thought, \nperfect for a sunglass campaign."},{"time":403487,"text":"People magazine did a great story."},{"time":405518,"text":"So it was circulating, \npeople were saying all this great stuff."},{"time":408586,"text":"It was fantastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410174,"text":"So I was getting calls, though."},{"time":411724,"text":"Getting calls from the U.K.,\nsaying, well we just saw this spread,"},{"time":414428,"text":"can you come photograph our \nkids with this condition?"},{"time":417725,"text":"We have a support group here, \ncan you come meet our families?"},{"time":420253,"text":"People in Africa were calling in the same."},{"time":422370,"text":"New Zealand, can you help \nus start a support group?"},{"time":424342,"text":"I'm like, fantastic! \nThis is great! Let's do it!"},{"time":427133,"text":"So I would travel in all these places,"},{"time":429527,"text":"as I was shooting \nand doing my commercial work,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":431951,"text":"I was at a local chapter conference \nin Philadelphia."},{"time":434436,"text":"Small family conference, \nabout 40 families,"},{"time":436503,"text":"did my presentation of kids with albinism,"},{"time":438934,"text":"this mom came up to me, and she said,"},{"time":440947,"text":"\"My son Randy, when he was a little boy,"},{"time":443281,"text":"he'd come home from school, \nand I could see the kids were teasing him,"},{"time":445848,"text":"and he'd be in tears."},{"time":447225,"text":"And I'd buy him an ice-cream cone,\nor a toy truck,"},{"time":450313,"text":"and he'd forget about it.\""},{"time":451655,"text":"She said, \"Now he's in high school.\nHe comes home from school,"},{"time":454574,"text":"I can see the pain, \nthe anguish in his eyes."},{"time":458018,"text":"He walks in, he walks right past me,"},{"time":460914,"text":"goes up to his room, slams the door,"},{"time":462482,"text":"and I don't see him until the next day."},{"time":464365,"text":"He's not going to want to be photographed,"},{"time":465976,"text":"he has zero self-esteem,"},{"time":467317,"text":"this kid has such poor body image,\nand he's just so shy."},{"time":472383,"text":"But if you could just show him \nphotographs of kids his own age,"},{"time":475852,"text":"so that he knows he's not alone.\""},{"time":478068,"text":"I'm like, \"Of course. Where is he? Show me!\""},{"time":480095,"text":"She points over to Randy."},{"time":481385,"text":"Now Randy's sitting there — \nhis pants are hanging down to here,"},{"time":483306,"text":"his underwear's hanging out, \nhe has this long, great big shirt,"},{"time":486158,"text":"he has ten earrings, he has a tattoo.\nHe's amazing, this kid."},{"time":489240,"text":"I crawl over to Randy."},{"time":490874,"text":"I'm like, \"Randy, \nI speak to moms and dads every single day,"},{"time":494244,"text":"terrified about the future \nof their kids with albinism."},{"time":497484,"text":"All they have to do \nis take one look at you,"},{"time":499169,"text":"and they're going to be fine."},{"time":500403,"text":"Please let me take a photo of you."},{"time":501957,"text":"Your mother said, she told me,"},{"time":503122,"text":"that you didn't want to be photographed.\""},{"time":504848,"text":"He said, \"Rick, \nwhat do you mean?"},{"time":506685,"text":"You have to understand, I'm 16 years old."},{"time":509402,"text":"I don't talk to my mother.\""},{"time":511139,"text":"And then he said, \"I want to be photographed."},{"time":514727,"text":"I want to show the world that who I am,"},{"time":516784,"text":"with my albinism, but also \nother things about me —\""},{"time":518192,"text":"You see how shy he was."},{"time":519686,"text":"Very, very shy, Randy."},{"time":521183,"text":"But Randy created, \nearly days in this idea,"},{"time":523895,"text":"of this nonprofit group \nPositive Exposure,"},{"time":526027,"text":"the idea of networking stories,"},{"time":527549,"text":"sharing experiences and the images \naround the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530939,"text":"I'll kind of quickly go through the album."},{"time":533419,"text":"I was very interested, at that point,"},{"time":535192,"text":"getting calls from everybody in the world,"},{"time":537251,"text":"to find out more about this idea, \na message, about albinism,"},{"time":540559,"text":"or perceptions of people in communities \nabout this syndrome, albinism."},{"time":544795,"text":"So I started hearing about stigmas, \nand discrimination,"},{"time":548322,"text":"so what I looked at is really trying \nto explore cultural perceptions"},{"time":551695,"text":"and attitudes towards this condition."},{"time":554221,"text":"This is my friend [unclear], \nwho's a Kuna Indian"},{"time":556928,"text":"in the San Blas region of the world,"},{"time":559268,"text":"the San Blas region of Panama."},{"time":562602,"text":"She's extraordinary."},{"time":564064,"text":"So the incidence of albinism \nis about one in 20,000 worldwide."},{"time":567618,"text":"In the Kuna Indian, it's one in 125, \nthe highest incidence in the world."},{"time":572858,"text":"We went to Fiji, actually, where we \nfound out at the turn of the 19th century,"},{"time":576458,"text":"a tribe could not hold their territory"},{"time":578767,"text":"unless they had somebody with albinism \nin a powerful political position."},{"time":583225,"text":"My great friend Keke, \nI photographed in New Zealand,"},{"time":586022,"text":"she's from India, from Delhi,"},{"time":588769,"text":"but her family left Delhi \nbecause she was getting death threats."},{"time":592037,"text":"Now I'm thinking, \nthis is horrible that they had to move,"},{"time":594295,"text":"because she's eight years old."},{"time":595733,"text":"And we actually started \na support group in Delhi,"},{"time":598072,"text":"we found out that there are many kids\nthat we worked with in their communities,"},{"time":600946,"text":"after we started this group in India,"},{"time":602829,"text":"that have had really positive experiences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605078,"text":"So one of the things \nwe want to make very clear"},{"time":607137,"text":"is that we're not making generalizations"},{"time":609099,"text":"about a community or a culture,"},{"time":610611,"text":"and their reaction \nto people that are different."},{"time":612545,"text":"Keke's experiences were very different,"},{"time":614235,"text":"but we've met many kids there"},{"time":615827,"text":"that have been embraced \nby their communities throughout India."},{"time":619209,"text":"A great friend Sue Anna from Korea."},{"time":623458,"text":"Tom, who was just adopted \nby an American family, from China,"},{"time":627414,"text":"This is my great friend \nHarry from Puerto Rico."},{"time":630685,"text":"And Natalia."},{"time":631928,"text":"She and I started \nthe first albinism society in Russia."},{"time":635591,"text":"Maizan and her sister \nand mom in Malaysia."},{"time":639726,"text":"Ceara. All she ever wanted to do \nwas be a dancer."},{"time":642725,"text":"She was told that \nbecause of her visual impairment,"},{"time":644841,"text":"she'll never dance."},{"time":646217,"text":"She'll never be able to follow \nthe choreography or the dance steps."},{"time":649283,"text":"She's like, they said, \nfind another love, another passion."},{"time":653804,"text":"She's like, no."},{"time":655221,"text":"She's New Zealand's Celtic dance champion,"},{"time":657367,"text":"and just started a school for dance \nfor kids with visual impairment."},{"time":660647,"text":"I'm going to zip through this. \nRoz, from Australia."},{"time":663850,"text":"I spend a lot of time in Africa,"},{"time":665534,"text":"where there's a high incidence \nof mortality associated with albinism,"},{"time":668310,"text":"due to skin cancer."},{"time":669956,"text":"This is my friend Siri, \nwho when she was born,"},{"time":672603,"text":"the father's family \nput her out of the house,"},{"time":674504,"text":"thinking she was cursed."},{"time":676865,"text":"and Mom, not knowing what to do,"},{"time":678686,"text":"put Siri in the sun to get her dark \nlike her brothers and sisters."},{"time":681771,"text":"So you can see, it's all sun damage."},{"time":684672,"text":"A lot of kids that I met throughout Africa\nwere put in special schools,"},{"time":688980,"text":"schools for the blind,"},{"time":691168,"text":"not because the tools were better there \nfor kids with visual impairment,"},{"time":694237,"text":"but more importantly, \nbecause the teasing was so great,"},{"time":696640,"text":"the discrimination is so great,"},{"time":697879,"text":"these kids don't do well \nin mainstream schools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701218,"text":"I started an albinism society in Kenya \nwith my friend C.K.,"},{"time":704688,"text":"who actually went to a mainstream school."},{"time":706188,"text":"I'm like, C.K., how is it possible \nyou went to a mainstream school?"},{"time":709092,"text":"Nobody in Africa goes \nto mainstream schools."},{"time":710943,"text":"She said, \"It's because \nof my twin sister, Delphine.\""},{"time":713383,"text":"Fantastic. She said Delphine would get \nall the work off the board,"},{"time":717237,"text":"the things I couldn't see, \nshe'd help me with it."},{"time":719627,"text":"If the type was too small, \nshe'd blow it up for me, she said."},{"time":722276,"text":"But more importantly, \nwhen kids would tease me,"},{"time":724408,"text":"Delphine would beat them up."},{"time":726136,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":727734,"text":"But on a sadder note, I was spending \na lot of time in Tanzania,"},{"time":730093,"text":"where witch doctors are saying,"},{"time":731280,"text":"bring me the bones of an albino,"},{"time":733490,"text":"and I'll make a potion\nthat will make you rich."},{"time":735760,"text":"So we're working very closely \nwith the government there,"},{"time":737922,"text":"I've been there six times \nin the last two years,"},{"time":739638,"text":"to create public awareness programs\nto save these kids."},{"time":745862,"text":"This is the dancer."},{"time":747711,"text":"This is in the Shinyanga region."},{"time":749900,"text":"This is one of the visuals \nthat we created in East Africa,"},{"time":753739,"text":"trying to fight and educate the public."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756718,"text":"I received the Art of Reporting award, \nfrom an organization"},{"time":759986,"text":"called the Chromosome 18 Registry."},{"time":762040,"text":"The larger organization \nwas the Genetic Alliance,"},{"time":765789,"text":"which was a coalition \nof all the genetic support groups,"},{"time":767768,"text":"and it was the award \nfor the Life magazine piece."},{"time":770788,"text":"The president at the time said,"},{"time":772268,"text":"I'm also the founder and director"},{"time":773637,"text":"of the Chromosome 18 Research Society \nand Registry."},{"time":776346,"text":"I'm like, fantastic! \nThat's great. What's that?"},{"time":778587,"text":"She's like, well, if you have an anomaly \non your 18th chromosome,"},{"time":781803,"text":"then you have all kinds of problems \nand difficulties and challenges,"},{"time":785071,"text":"and then we look after you, \nthrough this support group, like NOAH is."},{"time":788387,"text":"So I'm like, that's great."},{"time":790462,"text":"She said, \nI see there's a universal message here,"},{"time":792427,"text":"about all kids with differences, \nso it's not just about albinism."},{"time":795094,"text":"Would you come and speak \nto our families in San Antonio"},{"time":797793,"text":"with these chromosome 18 anomalies?"},{"time":799472,"text":"I'm like, sure! \nI went back to them thinking,"},{"time":802102,"text":"what the hell is \na chromosome 18 anomaly?"},{"time":803502,"text":"I was an art major\nat the school of visual arts,"},{"time":804952,"text":"I had no idea."},{"time":806641,"text":"But I looked it up, \nthese are the images that I saw."},{"time":810070,"text":"I'm thinking, albinism was so easy, \nthis is going to be rough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812886,"text":"But I went to San Antonio,"},{"time":814961,"text":"walked down to the auditorium \nwhere the kids and young adults were,"},{"time":817596,"text":"opened the door, \nand I was instantly surrounded"},{"time":819488,"text":"by kids screaming with laughter."},{"time":820920,"text":"There were kids with cleft palates, \nkids with mobility issues,"},{"time":824404,"text":"feeding tubes, trachs, \nbut they were kids, first and foremost."},{"time":827346,"text":"That's Rebecca and Pauline."},{"time":828917,"text":"My great friend, that's Ellington. \nHe's awesome."},{"time":832593,"text":"Remy."},{"time":834247,"text":"That's Emory."},{"time":836693,"text":"Byron."},{"time":838386,"text":"Taylor."},{"time":840248,"text":"Elizabeth."},{"time":841795,"text":"And my great friend Sean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":843872,"text":"So we decided at that point \nto involve other organizations"},{"time":847733,"text":"to be part of this larger exhibition"},{"time":850975,"text":"that was going to be sent out from \nthe People's Genome Celebration in 2001."},{"time":856187,"text":"The National Human Genome Research \nInstitute and the Genetic Alliance"},{"time":859435,"text":"invited me to create an exhibition \nat the Smithsonian,"},{"time":862476,"text":"commemorating the mapping \nof the human genome."},{"time":864666,"text":"So we actually invited \nother genetic support groups"},{"time":867109,"text":"to be part of this exhibition, \nnot just on albinism, but all groups,"},{"time":870428,"text":"again illustrating \nthe universal applicability."},{"time":872874,"text":"I saw these images \nfrom the Marfan Foundation,"},{"time":875102,"text":"these kids grow very, very tall, \nat risk of an aortic dissection,"},{"time":878574,"text":"but they're amazing kids,\nand I thought, how gorgeous."},{"time":880891,"text":"And I understood \nthe importance of this image,"},{"time":883811,"text":"how important it was \nto show how beautiful,"},{"time":885920,"text":"and to show how the image presents itself."},{"time":887919,"text":"But isn't there another way to show it?"},{"time":889778,"text":"Because nobody, and I've photographed \nthousands of kids now,"},{"time":891940,"text":"with Marfan Syndrome,"},{"time":893022,"text":"and nobody stands like this, \nwith a portable black bar."},{"time":896055,"text":"It's extraordinary. \nSo we decided to put them in a pool,"},{"time":898734,"text":"show Billy swimming --\n[\"Bill with Marfan Syndrome\"] --"},{"time":900980,"text":"show how it presents itself, \nbut keep going,"},{"time":902897,"text":"and keep presenting how these kids look,"},{"time":905574,"text":"but put the humanity \nback in these gorgeous images."},{"time":908481,"text":"I only have a few seconds here, \nso I'm going to go through."},{"time":911709,"text":"Cool girls at the Costello Conference."},{"time":913528,"text":"These are great friends \nDanielle and Maggie,"},{"time":915628,"text":"who actually met \nat the last Costello Conference."},{"time":917958,"text":"For both, the first time they ever met \nanybody with the same syndrome."},{"time":920870,"text":"They go to the same conferences \nevery year and I go and photograph them."},{"time":924701,"text":"And this year, \nthey were there again in Florida,"},{"time":926187,"text":"but this time it's a little different."},{"time":928103,"text":"They're gangsters now. (Laughter)\nBut they're pretty amazing kids."},{"time":931299,"text":"I just want to talk very briefly \nabout this really great kid,"},{"time":937550,"text":"to talk very briefly about a project \nthat we're taking these images,"},{"time":941793,"text":"and bringing them into high schools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":943348,"text":"I can photograph a great kid in my studio,"},{"time":946068,"text":"and she's having a brilliant time, \nand she feels 10,000 feet tall."},{"time":949267,"text":"By the time she leaves my studio \nand gets to Park Avenue,"},{"time":953282,"text":"five people point at her, \npoint at her birthmark,"},{"time":955583,"text":"or at her white hair, or her wheelchair."},{"time":958094,"text":"So we have to make it relevant \nfor all of us, for all these kids,"},{"time":961213,"text":"to make people understand what the idea \nof celebrating diversity actually means."},{"time":965606,"text":"So we started a project \ncalled the PEARLS Project,"},{"time":967512,"text":"where these photographs \nare going into high schools,"},{"time":969986,"text":"and the kids that are in the images \nare blogging,"},{"time":972333,"text":"and the students\nare following their blogs."},{"time":974460,"text":"And they all have \nthese great video intros."},{"time":976329,"text":"I just want to give you this last one, \nand this is actually Byron,"},{"time":978885,"text":"who is actually one of our bloggers."},{"time":980997,"text":"(Video) Byron: Hi, my name is Byron."},{"time":982899,"text":"I live in the D.C. area. I'm 14."},{"time":985601,"text":"When I was 10 months old,"},{"time":987339,"text":"I had a left hemispherectomy."},{"time":990375,"text":"I had the left half of my brain removed,"},{"time":994277,"text":"because I have something \ncalled Sturge-Weber Syndrome."},{"time":999063,"text":"I wear a brace\non my right leg and right arm."},{"time":1003835,"text":"I only see out of \nthe right side of each eye,"},{"time":1007394,"text":"so sometimes it's harder \nfor me to see things on the right side."},{"time":1014875,"text":"So playing sports can be frustrating, \nbecause I might not see a ball coming."},{"time":1027122,"text":"I didn't see that coming. Excuse me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1030224,"text":"Rick Guidotti: So we're using \nall the visual art"},{"time":1033700,"text":"to change public perceptions \nthrough these great kids."},{"time":1036454,"text":"I feel as an artist, \nit's my responsibility."},{"time":1038751,"text":"I know that when I was a kid,"},{"time":1039992,"text":"and I saw someone that was different \nwalking down the street,"},{"time":1042553,"text":"If I stared, I got slapped by my mom."},{"time":1044846,"text":"So the idea was\nif you don't stare, look away."},{"time":1048300,"text":"And I think as an artist, \nit's my responsibility,"},{"time":1050317,"text":"and all of our responsibilities,"},{"time":1052004,"text":"to steady that gaze a little bit longer."},{"time":1054242,"text":"Because you stand there, \nand you'll see a difference."},{"time":1057543,"text":"You'll start seeing beauty \nin that difference."},{"time":1059979,"text":"And you'll start seeing \nbeautiful gorgeousness,"},{"time":1062072,"text":"and then this light just spreads, \nand once you're enlightened,"},{"time":1065059,"text":"it just changes your whole world."},{"time":1066736,"text":"It's about seeing \nthe beauty in all differences."},{"time":1069186,"text":"Thank you so much, I'm sorry I ran over."},{"time":1070667,"text":"Thank you guys, thank you."}]}]}